  "prompt": "I want to change my name in my class 10 CBSE certificate, but I'm currently living in KSA and I'm not an Indian. What should I do?",
  "response": "Changing your name in your class 10 CBSE certificate while living outside India can be a complex process, especially if you are not an Indian citizen. Here are the steps you should consider:\n\n1. **Contact CBSE Authorities**: Reach out to the Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) through their official website or via email. Explain your situation and inquire about the process for name change corrections in the certificate. Obtain information about the required documents and procedures.\n\n2. **Required Documents**: Prepare the necessary documents. Typically, you may need:\n   - A copy of the class 10 certificate.\n   - Proof of the name change (legal documents such as a court order or an affidavit).\n   - Application form for name change (available on the CBSE website).\n   - Identification documents (passport, etc.).\n   - Payment of the prescribed fee.\n\n3. **Affidavit for Name Change**: Create an affidavit stating the reason and new name. This affidavit needs to be notarized. Consult with local legal experts for the format and notarization process, which might differ from country to country.\n\n4. **Gazette Notification**: If CBSE requires a gazette notification of the name change, you might need to get this published in the Indian Government\u2019s Gazette, which can be done online. Ensure you follow the specific guidelines for foreigners.\n\n5. **Forward Documents**: Send all the required documents to the CBSE office in India via courier or registered post. Keep track of the shipment for confirmation of delivery.\n\n6. **Follow-Up**: After the submission, regularly follow up with CBSE officials on the status of your application. Email and phone contact can help expedite the process.\n\n7. **Authorized Representative (Optional)**: If managing this from KSA is challenging, you might consider appointing a trusted friend or family member in India as your representative to liaise with CBSE on your behalf.\n\nAlways make sure to verify each step with the CBSE official guidelines to ensure compliance with their requirements.",
